---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n/ui';

const lang = 'en' as const;
---

<BaseLayout>
  <div class="page">
    <header class="masthead">
      <div class="masthead__inner">
        <div class="masthead__brand">
          <span class="kicker">{t(lang, 'meta.issue')} · {t(lang, 'meta.date')}</span>
          <h1 class="display display--mega">{t(lang, 'site.title')}</h1>
          <p class="masthead__sub">汪星宇</p>
        </div>
        <nav class="masthead__nav">
          <a href="#about">About</a>
          <a href="#fronts">Fronts</a>
          <a href="#soul">Soul</a>
          <a href="#stance">Stance</a>
          <a href="#pantheon">Pantheon</a>
          <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
          <a href="/" class="masthead__lang">中文</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <hr class="rule-thick" />

    <section class="cover">
      <span class="kicker">Cover · This Issue</span>
      <h2 class="display">Having seen the vastness<br />of heaven and earth,<br />still tender toward each green blade.</h2>
      <p class="dek">
        Nine years on the frontline of rural revitalization in China.
        AI explorer. Social-science researcher in the making.
        AI in one hand, the countryside in the other — running a "super one-person company."
      </p>
      <p class="byline">
        Editor · Will Wang / Set in Astro / Type · Source Serif &amp; Noto Serif SC
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="about" class="column">
      <span class="kicker">About · Column</span>
      <h3>Editor's note</h3>
      <div class="prose dropcap">
        <p>
          The first time I walked into the mountains of western Hunan in 2017,
          I didn't know I'd still be on that road nine years later.
          From a political-science classroom in New York to a fire pit in a Miao village,
          from <em>Rural Notes</em> to <em>Hills &amp; Seas Youth</em>,
          the work has been concrete and clumsy: make space for kids in the mountains
          to sit down and read, give kids in the city a reason to step into real countryside.
        </p>
        <p>
          From 2026 on, I'm reshaping myself into a "super one-person company."
          One hand uses AI as an amplifier, pushing what one person can produce past the threshold of an organization.
          The other keeps doing the rural work — cultural tourism, education nonprofits, industry incubation.
          The two fronts aren't a split. They're a feedback loop:
          AI makes rural complexity tractable; the countryside keeps AI applied to real people.
        </p>
        <p>
          The longer arc is a question I want to answer with social science and business logic together —
          <em>can systemic injustice be solved structurally?</em>
          So my eventual research direction is equity and equality.
          This site is a slow, ongoing record of that process.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="fronts" class="column fronts">
      <span class="kicker">Two Fronts · Main Lines</span>
      <h3>AI in one hand, the countryside in the other.</h3>
      <div class="fronts__grid">
        <article class="fronts__col">
          <p class="fronts__hand">Left hand</p>
          <h4>AI Explorer</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Stay on the frontier; probe the limits of what AI can do</li>
            <li>Use AI to massively extend one person's reach and impact</li>
            <li>Make the "super one-person company" a referenceable model</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="fronts__col">
          <p class="fronts__hand">Right hand</p>
          <h4>Rural Roots</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Rural Notes</strong> — a content vehicle between city and countryside</li>
            <li><strong>Hills &amp; Seas Youth</strong> — bringing young people back into real rural life</li>
            <li>Cultural tourism · education nonprofits · industry incubation</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="soul" class="column soul">
      <span class="kicker">Soul · Three Mottos</span>
      <h3>How I navigate</h3>
      <div class="soul__list">
        <blockquote class="pull-quote">
          Hold to your own way; do not unsettle the hearts of others.
          <span class="pull-quote__gloss">A rule for action — be true to yourself, but never trespass on someone else's ground.</span>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="pull-quote">
          Keep company with the bold-hearted; read in the spaces between the words.
          <span class="pull-quote__gloss">A rule for company and reading — value loyalty and lived experience; the world is the larger book.</span>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="pull-quote">
          Having seen the vastness of heaven and earth, still tender toward each green blade.
          <span class="pull-quote__gloss">A rule for compassion — even after grasping the whole, stay gentle with every particular.</span>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="stance" class="column">
      <span class="kicker">Stance · What I Push Against</span>
      <h3>What I refuse to normalize</h3>
      <ol class="stance">
        <li>
          <h4>Performative poverty alleviation</h4>
          <p>
            Formalism doesn't only waste data. It costs the dignity of the people being served.
            I use frontline cases to puncture it.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>The arrogance of large capital</h4>
          <p>
            The casual erasure and systemic extraction of vulnerable groups
            should not be naturalized as the cost of doing business.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>The meaning vacuum among young people</h4>
          <p>
            "Lying flat" and nihilism are symptoms, not the problem itself.
            Science and action can offer a different answer.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="pantheon" class="column">
      <span class="kicker">Pantheon · Touchstones</span>
      <h3>People I look up to</h3>
      <div class="pantheon">
        <div class="pantheon__group">
          <p class="pantheon__label">Politics · Social vision</p>
          <ul>
            <li><span>Zhou Enlai</span><em>relentless service</em></li>
            <li><span>Karl Marx</span><em>class insight</em></li>
            <li><span>Barack Obama</span><em>oratory and change</em></li>
            <li><span>Zhang Guimei</span><em>the lamp-lighter</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pantheon__group">
          <p class="pantheon__label">Scholarship · Rural roots</p>
          <ul>
            <li><span>Fei Xiaotong</span><em>differential mode of association</em></li>
            <li><span>Shen Congwen</span><em>human grace in the borderlands</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pantheon__group">
          <p class="pantheon__label">Innovation · Action</p>
          <ul>
            <li><span>Elon Musk</span><em>first principles</em></li>
            <li><span>Steve Jobs</span><em>product as Zen</em></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="knowledge" class="column">
      <span class="kicker">Method · Knowledge Map</span>
      <h3>How I think</h3>
      <p class="dek">
        Social science as ground, business as bone, complexity science as method,
        brain science as obsession, the countryside as the field.
      </p>
      <ol class="kmap">
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">01</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Social-science foundation</h4>
            <p>Roughly six years of training in international politics and IR at Fudan University and NYU. Reads reality through institutions, power, social structure, inequality, and globalization.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">02</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Business and management</h4>
            <p>Coursework across multiple business schools — Peking University Guanghua, Tsinghua PBCSF among them. Frames problems through resource allocation, organizational design, and business models.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">03</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Frontier science</h4>
            <p>Gaoshan Academy fellow · Shoucheng Zhang Scholar. Currently mapping the last 20 years of Nobel-related advances to assemble a working frame for modern science.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">04</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Complexity &amp; network science</h4>
            <p>Reads social and scientific problems through systems, networks, feedback loops, nonlinearity, and emergence.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">05</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Motivation &amp; brain science</h4>
            <p>Long-running question: how does human motivation actually arise? Studies dopamine, habit formation, self-efficacy, cognitive reframing — and applies it to education and personal practice.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">06</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Rural revitalization in the field</h4>
            <p>Nine years on the ground. Pairs social-science theory with concrete Chinese rural cases to read structural problems and find paths to action.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="kmap__num">07</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Default analytical bias</h4>
            <p>Systems &gt; individual moralizing · complexity &gt; linear cause · cross-disciplinary &gt; single frame · practice &gt; pure abstraction.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="projects" class="column">
      <span class="kicker">Contents · This Issue</span>
      <h3>Selected Works</h3>
      <p class="dek">Project detail pages arrive in the next stage. Below is placeholder.</p>
      <ul class="toc">
        <li>
          <span class="toc__num">01</span>
          <span class="toc__title">Rural Notes</span>
          <span class="toc__dek">A content vehicle between city and countryside — stories, fieldwork, image.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="toc__num">02</span>
          <span class="toc__title">Hills &amp; Seas Youth</span>
          <span class="toc__dek">A youth nonprofit bringing young people back into real rural life.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <section id="contact" class="column">
      <span class="kicker">Mast · Colophon</span>
      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:wangxingyu.will@gmail.com">wangxingyu.will@gmail.com</a><br />
        GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/wxydayie8888" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@wxydayie8888</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
      <p class="byline">{t(lang, 'footer.colophon')}</p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: var(--page-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--sp-6) var(--gutter) var(--sp-9);
  }

  .masthead__inner {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
    gap: var(--sp-5);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: var(--sp-4) 0 var(--sp-5);
  }
  .masthead__brand .display { margin: 0; }
  .masthead__sub {
    margin: var(--sp-1) 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    color: var(--gray);
  }
  .masthead__nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--sp-5);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--fs-base);
  }
  .masthead__nav a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
  }
  .masthead__nav a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--vermilion);
    color: var(--vermilion);
  }
  .masthead__lang {
    font-variant: small-caps;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  }

  .cover {
    padding: var(--sp-8) 0 var(--sp-7);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }

  .column { padding: var(--sp-6) 0; }
  .column h3 { margin: 0 0 var(--sp-5); }

  .fronts__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-7);
    margin-top: var(--sp-5);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .fronts__col h4 { margin: 0 0 var(--sp-3); font-size: var(--fs-lg); }
  .fronts__col ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1em; line-height: var(--lh-loose); }
  .fronts__hand {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-kicker);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--vermilion);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-2);
  }
  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .fronts__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--sp-6); }
  }

  .soul__list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-7);
    padding: var(--sp-5) 0;
  }

  .stance {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: stance;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--sp-5);
  }
  .stance li {
    counter-increment: stance;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--sp-5);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
  .stance li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .stance li::before {
    content: counter(stance, decimal-leading-zero);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--vermilion);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  }
  .stance h4 { margin: 0 0 var(--sp-2); font-size: var(--fs-md); }
  .stance p { margin: 0; max-width: var(--measure); }

  .pantheon {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--sp-7);
    margin-top: var(--sp-4);
  }
  .pantheon__label {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-kicker);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--vermilion);
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-3);
    padding-bottom: var(--sp-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
  .pantheon__group ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; line-height: var(--lh-loose); }
  .pantheon__group li {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    padding: var(--sp-1) 0;
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .pantheon__group span {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--fs-base);
  }
  .pantheon__group em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    text-align: right;
  }
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .pantheon { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--sp-5); }
  }

  .kmap {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--sp-5) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
  .kmap li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3.5rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    padding: var(--sp-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
  .kmap__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--vermilion);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  }
  .kmap h4 { margin: 0 0 var(--sp-2); font-size: var(--fs-md); }
  .kmap p { margin: 0; color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: var(--measure); }

  .toc {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
  .toc li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr 2fr;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    padding: var(--sp-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
  .toc__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--vermilion);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
  }
  .toc__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
  }
  .toc__dek {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: var(--fs-base);
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .toc li { grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr; }
    .toc__dek { grid-column: 2; margin-top: var(--sp-1); }
  }

  .footer {
    margin-top: var(--sp-9);
    padding-top: var(--sp-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }
</style>
